	   <a name=100735935888642></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100735935888642><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=100735935888642>Feign Death</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=100735935888642#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=89270><span id= >GarathBlackhawk</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>14 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Dec 3rd 1:02 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.75]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Here are a few things I have noticed using FD, and a few of my own questions I hope others can answer. First and most important, practise abjuration at level 15 with endure cold, and get it up to speed! Keep this skill maxed! If you get 15 points below your max, you are too low, start practising again.<br><br>Ok your 30th lvl now and you have one of the best spells in the game, not only will this save your life, you can handle rear guard duty when your group needs to run, and you may even live! You can also use it to break up mobs if there are too many to handle at once (I'm just now working on this, so I hope for input from more experienced players).<br><br>Feign Death is tied to two skills, Abjuration and Channeling. Abjuration will determine your success at casting, Channeling will help you to continue casting if you get interrupted.<br>You can successfully cast FD but the MOB is not fooled, if this happens you see the dreaded, Soandso has fallen to the floor, message. If this happens the MOB will continue to smack you around. <br>You can successfully cast FD but the MOB is still in the process of hitting you. If this happens the MOB believes you are dead until the attack hits. Once you take damage, they know you are faking and continue the attack. This is most apparent when the MOB is a caster, if you see them start to cast a spell after you cast your FD, get ready for some pain. The REALLY bad thing about this, is that FD takes a full 15 seconds before you can recast! <br>Once you FD the mob will drift back to their spawn point. MOBs under 35th lvl will generally forget about you after a FD. Those above will usually not forget about you, especially if they took damage (I have only seen this once so far, but I'm only 40 at the time of this posting). <br>You can FD on a MOB even if they are affected by a DOT you cast. <br>I'd like to hear how others get out of a FD, I'm ashamed to say it took me a lvl or two to find a fast way out, I use /sit off (or your sit button) to quickly get back to my feet. I haven't really tested whether your HP and mana come back at the sitting or standing rate, so if someone else wants to give some feedback I'd appreciate it.<br><br>Pulling with FD looks to be a cool new way to break up multiple MOB's. I have just started trying this, but here is what I've tried so far. If you have a large pack of MOB's, pull the entire crew to a safe spot. Feign Death on them...make sure you are facing the way you came from. The MOB starts to leave singly or in pairs. If you change your view so that you see the surrounding area, you can see how far off the other MOBs have gone. You should end up with the last one or two MOB's standing around when all the others have left far enough away that you (or your party) can attack. Just remeber that higher lvl MOBs might remember you when you come out of FD. You may need to camp or zone to clear aggro while your party takes out the MOB.<br><br>Much of this information was based on observations from others on these topics, so thanks to those who have posted on this before!<br><br>BTW don't just use endure cold as practise, Goblin shammies and wizards use cold based spells, this does have a use other then practising, spend some time in SolA =)!<br>&nbsp;<br>Daemondred Dreamslayer 46th knight of Innoruuk<br>Luclin <br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=111176" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=111176</a></td></tr>
