	   <tr><td colspan=2>I highly doubt this. Not that I don't trust you Cannis but this idea of a hidden &quot;exp bar&quot; that advances your fd skill is just a bit too rich.<br><br>On the other hand, max out your abjuration for your level and then log a sessions of fd's. If what you say is true there should be a difference in success rate between fd session number 1-100 and fd session 101-200 ( number of attemps is based on a very approximate estimation of how many times you'd fd over the course of five levels and over five levels you should see a difference in success rate ). Until you have such a session I think it's a bit unnecessary to post the above. We all know how this game works, it wouldn't surprise me if two months from now I get told by some level 12 sk that I should spend hours using only fd to be a better puller =). In my 56 levels as a shadowknight I haven't seen or noticed anything to the effect of what you claimed. One thing is correct though, channeling has absolutely no effect the success of your attempt. It only increases the chance of you getting off the spell in the first place so that a skill check can be made and then it's decided if you fail or succeed ( don't underestimate the GM's abilities to speak convoluted ).<br><br>Kamlatir, 56 Revenant, Far Seekers, The Rathe.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
