e else over in the zone. &gt;<br>Nope, Wrong. This is a perfectly valid and appropriate technique that is NOT Unique To Druids And Rangers. Bard Fear-Kiting comes to mind. No, what all too often happens is some idiot either doesn't pay attention to what is happening just steps in and breaks the kite instead of ASKING if help is needed, or some idiot tries to KS a MoB. Are all kites well controlled? No. Do 'innocents' die in the game? Yes.&nbsp;&nbsp;BUt as a sweeping statement, very vapid, and not valid.<br><br>&lt;Well, I am finished.&gt;<br>I doubt taht very much.<br><br> &lt;I'm hoping for some allies in my argument (and war) against these two overplayed classes and I know there are many enemies out there. Sorry for the long rant&gt;<br>So, how do you _really_ feel about Druids and Rangers, huh? And, why the animosity?<br><br>Sadly, you miss the point. They are played because they are FUN. Well, my drood is, didn't like the ranger I had that much. Easy, well, yeah, sorta. But at 30 Ammy is less and less effective solo as a melee so I need to group more. And NO, this does not prove your thesis - it jsut means that the game is changing for me and I have to group more, which is one of the strengths of teh game. <br> <br><br><br><br>To quote Eidulon...<br>&lt;. <br><br>1. They can evac. Wizards can Nuke and evac. <br><br>2. They can buff. Shamans way out-buff druids, and way out-buff druids. (necros too) <br><br>3. They can heal. Clerics can way out-heal druids. &gt;<br><br>Yeah, but you get all this in ONE package. A drood makes a good backup healer, the healer to the primary healer for instance. Back up nuker too, the Planes help any summoned critter we go up against. And damage shield buffs. Melee sucks, droods get crap for weapons and armor. Yep. OK. Valid point and accepted (if not liked)limitation. But I like living by my brains rather than my brawn.<br><br>Actually, my REAL question to Civilchief ( who probably is neither), is: What th